article.description: — Kiree Huie's 20 points helped Idaho State defeat Lindenwood 76-70 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Huie scores 20, Idaho State beats Lindenwood 76-70
article.linkText: Huie scores 20, Idaho State beats Lindenwood 76-70
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho -- — Kiree Huie's 20 points helped Idaho State defeat Lindenwood 76-70 on Saturday night. Huie had nine rebounds for the Bengals (4-4). Isaiah Griffin was 5 of 11 shooting, including 1 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 7 for 10 from the line to add 18 points. Miguel Tomley was 3 of 9 shooting, including 2 for 7 from 3-point range, and went 2 for 4 from the line to finish with 10 points. Darius Beane led the way for the Lions (3-5) with 19 points and two steals. Lindenwood also got 14 points and seven rebounds from Keenon Cole. Jeremiah Talton also had 12 points and seven rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
